  "dct:title": "How to write an API",
  "dct:description": "This guide explains how to develop a custom API in NOMAD using the plugin system. It walks you through creating a FastAPI app, registering it as a plugin entry point using APIEntryPoint, and integrating it into a NOMAD distribution. You’ll learn how to define your API’s structure using a Python package, configure it with pyproject.toml, and build endpoints using FastAPI. This enables extending NOMAD with custom services accessible via new API routes. A working example and links to plugin development best practices are also provided.",
